      <p begin="00:39:37,829" end="00:39:42,838">- [Emilio] At Merck, HIV was an important<br xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>scientific target.</p>
      <p begin="00:39:44,081" end="00:39:46,221">HIV of course is a virus.</p>
      <p begin="00:39:46,221" end="00:39:49,997">In order for the virus to infect<br xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>an uninfected cell,</p>
      <p begin="00:39:50,359" end="00:39:54,307">it needs to construct itself<br xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>in a particular way.</p>
      <p begin="00:39:55,004" end="00:39:59,876">
        <span tts:fontStyle="italic">First, the viral RNA needs<br/>to transform itself into a DNA copy,</span>
