      </p>
      <p begin="00:40:21,869" end="00:40:25,804">
        <span tts:fontStyle="italic">of the viral life cycle,<br/>after the cell is already infected.</span>
      </p>
      <p begin="00:40:25,804" end="00:40:31,506">One of the steps that it takes is that<br xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>it makes a viral protein.</p>
      <p begin="00:40:31,506" end="00:40:36,187">It has to snip that viral protein<br xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>in very specific places.</p>
      <p begin="00:40:36,187" end="00:40:41,920">
        <span tts:fontStyle="italic">The resulting pieces self-assemble<br/>to make the viral particle.</span>
      </p>
      <p begin="00:40:41,920" end="00:40:45,782">
        <span tts:fontStyle="italic">And what does the snipping<br/>and what in fact controls the snipping,</span>
